Three Americans were on board an Adam Air plane that crashed in Indonesia.
The Boeing 737-400 disappeared between Java and Sulawesi, with up to 12 survivors.
Search and rescue efforts were criticized for being slow.
The plane likely crashed due to bad weather, killing at least 90 people.
The Indonesian Navy sent planes to retrieve victims.
Chinese Foreign Minister expressed condolences.
The cause of the crash remains unknown.
The tragedy marks the worst air disaster since 2005.
Families await news on the fate of their loved ones as investigations continue.
